sExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ely1665702755621.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ely1665702755621.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ely1665702755621.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ely1665702755621\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Creates or updates the specified document in storage.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ely1665702755621__topic_d127502e1_d127503e1_d127504e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127505e1_d127506e1_d127507e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.datastore.put</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Doc</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127508e1_d127509e1_d127510e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.datastore.put({_id:'songs_dsp',title:'Heroes'})</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ely1665702755621__section_w1397ab1b5b3_w1398ab1b5_w1399ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146610e73\">Arguments </h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"ely1665702755621__parml_o4j_msb_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">Doc</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">A pure JSON object, that is, a collection of name/value pairs. It must contain:<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ely1665702755621__ul_pmz_lsb_dwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ely1665702755621__li_d46259e1_d46260e1_d46261e1\">The document identifier: <code class=\"ph codeph\">_id:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ely1665702755621__li_d46262e1_d46263e1_d46264e1\">Any other data to be stored:\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">NameOfData</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>. </li>\n</ul></dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ely1665702755621__note_smz_lsb_dwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you try to store non-JSON data (for example, Date\n        objects) you may see inconsistent results.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ely1665702755621__section_w1400ab1b5b5_w1401ab1b5_w1402ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146610e117\">Return Value</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127520e1_d127521e1_d127522e1\">Returns a JavaScript Promise object with the response.\n        This includes a revision marker <code class=\"ph codeph\">_rev:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Otherwise, an error is returned. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ely1665702755621__section_w1403ab1b5b7_w1404ab1b5_w1405ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146610e135\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127529e1_d127530e1_d127531e1\">Whenever a data object is created or updated, a new\n        version of the document is created. It is distinguished from other versions by a revision\n        marker that is automatically added to the document as a field <code class=\"ph codeph\">_rev:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">String</var>. The revision marker contains a unique random number that is\n        updated each time the data object is updated, and is added to the response.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">When updating <var class=\"keyword varname\">Doc</var>, you must specify the revision to update.\n        </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ely1665702755621__section_k43_xrv_1dc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146610e156\">Example: Creating a document in offline storage </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127538e1_d127539e1_d127540e1\">When you create a new document in client-side storage,\n        you only need to specify the document identifier and the rest of the data to be stored:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ely1665702755621_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ely1665702755621__codeblock_lgm_wsb_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Uniface.datastore.put({\n _id: 'songs_dsp',\n title: 'Heroes'\n }).then(function (response) {\n // handle response\n }).catch(function (err) {\n console.log(err);\n });</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ely1665702755621__section_gj1_vrv_1dc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d146610e169\">Example: Updating a document in offline storage </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ely1665702755621__p_d127544e1_d127545e1_d127546e1\">When updating an existing document, you must first\n        retrieve it using <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.datastore.get</span>, so that you have the revision\n        number. You can then update the document, providing the document identifier, the revision,\n        and the data to be modified:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ely1665702755621_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ely1665702755621__codeblock_nvc_ysb_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">uniface.datastore.get('songs_dsp').then(function(doc) {\n return uniface.datastore.put({\n _id: 'songs_dsp',\n _rev: doc._rev,\n title: \"Let's Dance\"\n });\n }).then(function(response) {\n // handle response\n }).catch(function (err) {\n console.log(err);\n });</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etq1665702755550.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Client-Side Data Storage</a><p>Uniface dynamic server pages support client-side storage of data in a browser-based database, which makes it possible to save data locally when there is no connection to the server. This can be useful when you want to display read-only information that has previously been downloaded, or to save modified data until it can be synchronized or uploaded to the server.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "put() Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Creates or updates the specified document in storage. uniface.datastore.put ( Doc ) Example: uniface.datastore.put({_id:'songs_dsp',title:'Heroes'}) Arguments Doc A pure JSON object, that is, a collection of name/value pairs. It must contain: The document identifier: _id: String . Any other data to be stored: NameOfData : String . Note: If you try to store non-JSON data (for example, Date objects) you may see inconsistent results. Return Value Returns a JavaScript Promise object with the response. This includes a revision marker _rev: String . Otherwise, an error is returned. Description Whenever a data object is created or updated, a new version of the document is created. It is distinguished from other versions by a revision marker that is automatically added to the document as a field _rev: String . The revision marker contains a unique random number that is updated each time the data object is updated, and is added to the response. When updating Doc , you must specify the revision to update. Example: Creating a document in offline storage When you create a new document in client-side storage, you only need to specify the document identifier and the rest of the data to be stored: Explain this code Uniface.datastore.put({ _id: 'songs_dsp', title: 'Heroes' }).then(function (response) { // handle response }).catch(function (err) { console.log(err); }); Copy Example: Updating a document in offline storage When updating an existing document, you must first retrieve it using uniface.datastore.get , so that you have the revision number. You can then update the document, providing the document identifier, the revision, and the data to be modified: Explain this code uniface.datastore.get('songs_dsp').then(function(doc) { return uniface.datastore.put({ _id: 'songs_dsp', _rev: doc._rev, title: \"Let's Dance\" }); }).then(function(response) { // handle response }).catch(function (err) { console.log(err); }); Copy Related Links Client-Side Data Storage Uniface dynamic server pages support client-side storage of data in a browser-based database, which makes it possible to save data locally when there is no connection to the server. This can be useful when you want to display read-only information that has previously been downloaded, or to save modified data until it can be synchronized or uploaded to the server. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}